00:55:40,437 --> 00:56:09,057
No, that is the only position that is funded through ARPA, I'm sorry, and my language access. Yes, but they weren't finished, right? That's right. So as the DEI offers, the federal government doesn't care where you are housed, they just care who is your civil rights person. Those monies are not just for translation. If somebody wanted to attend a meeting and they needed ASL, they needed CART,

125
00:56:09,057 --> 00:56:33,695
has to go through ADA, that's funded with that. If they want to attend programming at the library or an event that the school is having, Pam already left, the senior center, those monies are used to pay for that service. So as ARPA funds finally, finally end,

126
00:56:34,505 --> 00:56:59,480
we will still see an additional increase in future years of that, that tail end of that for like the final, so that our future budget years level funding will just be like one more step up, but not very big, and then it'll be kind of finally ARPA's gone, okay, now we can expect to see this amount going forward.

127
00:56:59,682 --> 00:57:28,876
What I will say is that you should expect to see a new amount as of July 1st of next year, because ARPA ends this year. So what you're seeing is just a best guesstimate of what we'll need from January 1st of next year to June 26th of next year. Got it, half of next year. Half of next year. And then in the new fiscal year,

128
00:57:28,876 --> 00:57:56,551
You will definitely see an increase. And it also depends. There are things that we can't control, right? We can't control who's going to be moving into the city. We can't control how active and engaged our residents are going to want to be. The reality is, if you're doing a good job, your residents are going to want to be more engaged. And whilst your residents become more engaged, they're probably going to have different needs. For sure.

129
00:57:56,821 --> 00:58:22,792
You're a part time employee. You just have one part time employee correct. So you're like a one and a half employee department. Yes. And how many hours does Nick work. Is it Nick. It's Nick right. Yeah. Nicholas. Yes. Fifteen hours. Fifteen. OK. OK great. Those are all my questions. I appreciate you being here. Great. Do we have any other questions for Director Nwaje.

